<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/13401ATNSLDSHJQKBGBDBQSJVDPTKJJMG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Daniel Hersog Orchestra ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>A fascinating big-band experience with powerful vocals.</h1> <span><br/></span>Vancouver trumpeter and composer Daniel Hersog leads an adventurous jazz orchestra comprised of the cream of the Vancouver jazz community. <span class=\"ItalicText\">All About Jazz</span> calls Hersog “a major new compositional voice in jazz,” while <span class=\"ItalicText\">Jazz Times</span> notes his writing is “directly in the lineage of great jazz composers like Gil Evans.”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This performance features guest vocalist Darynn Dean, who studied with Herbie Hancock and Wayne Shorter and brings a commanding, soulful presence. Dean has sung alongside Hubert Laws, Poncho Sanchez, and Les McCann and has performed at Hollywood Bowl Jazz Festival, Kennedy Center and Walt Disney Concert Hall.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Together, Hersog and Dean deliver a thrilling big-band experience, blending sophisticated orchestral arrangements with expressive, powerful vocals—a performance for long-time jazz fans and new audiences alike. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Hersog’s 17-member orchestra features Brad Turner, Steve Kaldestad, Bruno Hubert, James Danderfer and Bernie Arai.  <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://youtu.be/5aeYsJSGSJs?si=QZd3Sfi6jBl_mzZC\">Watch Video here</a></h2><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">This concert is part of North Shore Jazz (June 19-28), presented by BlueShore at CapU in partnership with Vancouver International Jazz Festival.</span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-25T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/files/f2096b8f-225a-419a-a0b3-7ac29a66da73.jpg>;
