<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/14401ASTBHRJNMRVVCMLVMRRSGQMJPHLG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Ivan Hartle ";
  schema:description """
	<h1>Chill grooves and timeless soulful vibes.</h1><span><br/></span>Vancouver guitarist and singer-songwriter Ivan Hartle fuses a vintage acid-jazz sonic aesthetic with modern soul, R&B, and pop elements. Hartle draws inspiration from the classic soul sounds of Sam Cooke and Otis Redding, and newer artists like John Mayer and Leon Bridges. His smooth danceable grooves also recall 1990s band Jamiroquai.   <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Pivoting from a successful US college baseball career into music, Hartle’s standout album <span class=\"ItalicText\">A Place to Stay</span> has received considerable airplay on CBC and has amassed more than 10 million streams on Spotify. Hartle’s band includes guitarist and backing vocalist Matt Storm, drummer Trent Otter and bassist Yamil Chain-Haddad.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p4dPG96V2TQ\">Watch Video Here</a></h2><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">This FREE event takes place at Lynn Valley Village.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">This concert is part of North Shore Jazz (June 19-28), presented by BlueShore at CapU in partnership with Vancouver International Jazz Festival.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-21T13:00:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
