<http://www.spektrix.com/capilanouniversity/event/13601ABSCMSGQNLTCLGCSNLSTLGHSDRHB>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Krystle dos Santos ";
  schema:description """
	<h2>A joy-forward homage to the influential creator. </h2><span><br/></span>Backed by an all-star 11-piece ensemble comprising Vancouver's best musicians, including very special guest vocalists Janelle Reid and Josh Wyper, and recent <span class=\"ItalicText\">Canada's Got Talent</span> contestant Carsim Birmingham, Krystle Dos Santos guarantees nothing but the best from Stevie Wonder's five decades of hitmaking.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Performing the Wonder catalogue with deep groove and respect for the songs that shaped generations, Kyrstle’s band promises to deliver mind-blowing renditions of favourites including “Sir Duke,” “Isn’t She Lovely,” “Living for the City” and more. From dance-floor burners to soul-soaked ballads, expect bold harmonies, impeccable musicianship, and that unmistakable Stevie spirit that turns a concert into a room-wide singalong. Stevie’s catalogue brought joy to the world. This night brings the joy right back.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For 50 years, Stevie Wonder has been one of the brightest lights in contemporary soul, pop, R&B, and funk music. A perennial critic's favourite, with 25 Grammy's to his name, Stevie Wonder continues to represent the best of American music.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Vancouver-based singer-songwriter Krystal Dos Santos is known for her powerful soul, jazz, and R&B vocals and for her cabaret shows <span class=\"ItalicText\">Hey Viola</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">History of Motown</span>. At a Stevie Wonder concert, she volunteered to sing with the icon. Sitting beside him on his piano bench, <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-lGMTR7rxZU\">Krystle nailed it</a> . So, this concert was meant to be! For those who missed the debut of this sold-out concert in Vancouver last year, here’s your chance to catch it, or catch it again!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Band: <span><br/></span>Krystle Dos Santos - vocals<span><br/></span>Janelle Reid - vocals<span><br/></span>Josh Wyper - vocals<span><br/></span>Carsim Birmingham - vocals<span><br/></span>Jon Holisko - drums<span><br/></span>Liam MacDonald - percussion<span><br/></span>Cole Tinney - keys<span><br/></span>Gavin Youngash - guitar<span><br/></span>Phil Bell - bass<span><br/></span>Kent Wallace - trumpet <span><br/></span>Mike Allen - saxophone <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=erFLuda8yTA\">Watch Video here</a></h2><span><br/></span><h2>Sponsored by WAVE 98.3</h2> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">This concert is part of North Shore Jazz (June 19-28), presented by BlueShore at CapU in partnership with Vancouver International Jazz Festival.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-26T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
